=== Noun phrase ===
'''[[lame]] [[duck]]''' (''plural'' '''lame ducks''')
# {{italbrac|colloquial}} a person or thing that is helpless, [[inefficient]], [[disabled]], or a [[monkey]].
# {{italbrac|US politics}} elected official who has lost the recent election or is not [[eligible]] for [[reelection]] and is [[marking time]] until leaving office
#* Congressman Jones was a '''lame duck''' and did not vote on many issues that were important to his [[constituent]]s.

